 The price of the OPEC basket of thirteen crudes stood at $90.46 a barrel on Tuesday, compared with $90.89 the previous day, according to OPEC Secretariat calculations. The figure for Tuesday however represents a shortfall of 0.47% or $0.43 per barrel compared with the price on Monday. The OPEC Reference Basket of Crudes is made up of Saharan Blend (Algeria), Girassol (Angola), Djeno (Congo), Zafiro (Equatorial Guinea), Rabi Light (Gabon), Iran Heavy (Islamic Republic of Iran), Basra Light (Iraq). Others are Kuwait Export (Kuwait), Es Sider (Libya), Bonny Light (Nigeria), Arab Light (Saudi Arabia), Murban (UAE) and Merey (Venezuela). 